body: For sale is a 1988 Chevy Camaro IROC Z28 with a 57L  This is 99 finished and is able to driveIt does need some final tuning I will do my best to describe the vehicle information below I am an ASE master certified technician and have done all the enginetrans work myself  Engine  Freshly built 350 bored 0030 over with 1051 domed hypereutectic pistons The heads are shaved 0010 and there has been a mild porting job done on them as well as 16 ratio roller rockers The valves valve guides valve seats seals springs studs retainers locks pushrods and all other hardware has been replaced on them These heads are nicely rebuild and everything including block was magnafluxed and checked for cracks as well as all spring heights and tensions check and adjusted as needed The engine block was bored 0030 over and new domed 1051 pistons and rings installed The engine has all new bearings and seals throughout as well as freeze plugs All ring gaps were checked and adjusted and a nice honing job was done before installing the pistons All studsbolts have been replaced with ARP hardened hardware New high volume oil pump and a new oil pump drive and pickup tube were also installed The cam is a new 292 duration Competition cams camshaft with matched hydraulic lifters and double roller timing chain An aluminum high volume water pump was installed with a 190 F thermostat The distributor is an HEI setup with an extra high voltage coil installed The intake is an aluminum edelbrock 4 barrel and the carb is a 650 cfm edelbrock The mechanical fuel pump was removed and replaced with an electric inline pump with a fuel pressure regulator before the carb The engine has wrapped block hugger headers installed and high performance spark plug wires This engine has a very nice lope to it at idle and is set up to pull strongly to about 6500 rpm It will run on high octane pump gas just fine  Trans  The transmission is a newly rebuilt 700R4 with a stage 2 shift kit installed All clutches bands and seals have been replaced as well as the drum The trans was checked on a transmission dyno and when the TV is at max it will shift VERY firmly at 6000 RPM The stall converter is a 2800 stall with lock up clutch  Vehicle  The car has new wheel bearings brakes lines front calipers tires dual exhaust with 3 inch tips its loud Its also has new polyurethane engine and trans mounts much stiffer and stronger than the OE The transmission has its own dedicated cooler separate from the radiator and the vehicle has 2 electric fans on a toggle switch for cooling The fuel pump is also on a toggle switch for safety since I had planned to drag race this car The interior of the car has new matching seat covers the original seats were showing a little wear and also a new headliner The dash is intact with no weathering cracks and all door lockswindowslights work fine The car is missing a radioantenna as well as the ashtray The brake system has been changed over to manual brakes due to the wild cam in the car I wanted to make sure that vacuum was not an issue and didnt trust running a vacuum reserve canister It stops fine but takes a little more pressure than a power assist system I still have the power system that will go with the car should you chose to change it back All in all it is a very complete car that runs well and is ready to go fast I have broken the engine in properly and the vehicle does not smoke The enginetrans only have about 10 15 hrs on them and only about 100 miles since completion The drivers door does not match perfectly due to the fact that there was a large dent in the door and I replaced it with another that I had Also some small spots on the front bumper are showing the yellow plastic where the paint has chipped off The car really doesnt need a paint job as the paint is in really good shape just a few spots and the door could use touched up by a good paint person The clear coat is starting to peel a little also  Please call two56 six42 one339 for more details

body: Thank you for inquiring about teaching in China  We understand that traveling to a foreign country to teach can be a very difficult decision Trying to find the right contract to teach in China can be quite challenging Many schools in China have unfair business practices and offer unfair contracts It is hard to know who to trust  We are an American organization that is designed to protect the rights of Americans that want to teach in China Our top concern is that people sign a fair contract to teach at a safe and legal school in China We negotiate contracts nationwide at all age levels including university The process of finding a legitimate position in China can be difficult and stressful Our goal is to make the process of gaining employment in China as simple as possible  MUST READ To help save time we have added some answers to Frequently Asked Questions These answers are standard for REAL schools in China  How long are the contracts  A standard contract is two semesters Fall Spring The duration of the contracts are 10 months long which includes two months vacation The start dates are September 1st and March 1st  What is the pay  The average pay of a standard contract is 4000RMB6000RMB a month for teaching 1620 hours a week Every teacher also receives a free private fully furnished apartment  The contracts are designed with low working hours so people will enjoy the experience When contracts start to exceed 20 hours per week the stress of the position increases exponentially In China your fellow Chinese teachers will make around 2000RMB for teaching 40 hours
